{"id":"mikloth","term":"Mikloth","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Staves. (1.) An officer under Dodai, in the time of David and Solomon (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 27:4\">1 Chr. 27:4</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) A Benjamite (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:32\">1 Chr. 8:32</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 9:37\">9:37</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 9:38\">38</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 27:4","1 Chronicles 8:32","1 Chronicles 9:37","1 Chronicles 9:38"]}